GAS LIQUIDS: PROPANE STILL CLIMBING

   December non-TET propane was done at 38.50 cts at Mt Belvieu in the
morning. But trade thinned with many players leaving early for the New Year
holiday.
   A trader bought normal butane at 38.50 cts for December. January normal
butane sold at 39.50 cts.
   Activity at Conway was extremely quiet. December Warren bbl of natural
gasoline sold at 41.75 cts and 42.00 cts.

Copyright 1996 The McGraw-Hill Companies



