January 5, 1996

LEAST-COST PLANNING: Oregon PUC Finds Idaho Power Reasonable

The Oregon PUC on December 29 acknowledged Idaho Power Co.'s (IP)
least-cost plan, which implements new conservation programs and
system efficiency improvements, continues efforts to relicense its
hydroelectric plants, and continues solar and windpower
development.

PUC acknowledgement of a least-cost plan means that the plan seems
reasonable to the PUC at the time, but favorable ratemaking
treatment is not guaranteed. It gives considerable weight in the
ratemaking process to utility actions that are consistent with
acknowledged plans.



