UK GAS REPORT via NewsNet
January 12, 1996

SOME GAS PRICES LINKED TO PRICE OF ELECTRICITY

It appears some companies supplying gas to power plants have been
offering contracts where the gas price is linked to the price of
electricity in the pool, thus protecting generators from a price
squeeze following changes in the electricity price.

This is seen as a marketing tool to secure sales in a market under
pressure from falling gas prices and surplus supplies.  It carries
risks of large losses for the gas supplier and such deals may be
offered at a premium.

Scottish Hydro is one generator that is believed to have agreed a gas
contract with around 40% linked to the electricity pool price.

Gas prices are more usually linked to an indicator such as the retail
price index.



