BRITISH GAS ANNOUNCES APPOINTMENT OF DIRECTOR

British Gas has announced the appointment of Patricia Mann as a non-
executive director of the company.

She is currently a vice president international of J Walker Thompson Co
Ltd, which she joined in 1959, and director of public affairs for its
UK Group. She has wide experience of consumer affairs, competition and
regulatory issues, and corporate governance.

Mann has had previous involvement with the gas industry, pre and post
privatisation, having served as a member of the Gas Consumers Council
from 1981 -1990.

She also has a wide knowledge of competition and regulatory issues,
having been a member of the Monopolies and Mergers Commission for nine
years from 1984-1993, said BG.



