NEW CHAIRMAN OF NATIONAL CONSUMER COUNCIL

David Hatch became chairman of the National Consumer Council (NCC) on 1
January.

Hatch's appointment is for a term of three years, requiring a
commitment of two days a week at a salary of #21,000.

He takes over from Lady Judith Wilcox, whose recent appointment to the
House of Lords was thought to conflict with her role at NCC.

Hatch has been involved in the television and radio industry since the
1960s.



