Low VOC Cleaner Used Automotive Refinishing

Du Pont (Wilmington, DE 19898; Tel 302/774-1000) has  a patent for
a low volatile organic compound (VOC) cleaner.  The composition
described in US Patent 5,230,821 was issued to John C. Larson and
Gary L. Horton on July 27, 1993.  It includes an aqueous emulsion
of a non-aromatic organic phase stabilized with a blend of
surfactants.  The emulsion is characterized by a low content of
VOC's and superior cleaning properties.  It is particularly useful
for removing water- and organic solvent-soluble materials from
automotive surfaces being refinished.




